Cherry_including_sour_Powdery_mildew={'r0':"Cherry Powdery mildew is a fungal disease that affects cherries, causing a white powdery growth on the leaves, fruit, and stems. Here are some remedies for powdery mildew:",'r1':"There are several home remedies for cherry powdery mildew:",'r2':"Baking soda solution: Mix 1 tablespoon of baking soda and 1 tablespoon of horticultural oil in 1 gallon of water. Spray the solution on the infected leaves and branches.",'r3':"Neem oil: Mix 2.5 mL of neem oil in 1 liter of water and spray the solution on the infected parts of the plant.",'r4':"Garlic spray: Blend 3 cloves of garlic with 1 liter of water, strain and spray on the infected area.",'r5':"Potassium bicarbonate: Mix 1 teaspoon of potassium bicarbonate with 1 liter of water and spray on the infected area.",'r6':"It's important to regularly monitor your cherry tree for signs of powdery mildew and to apply these remedies at the first sign of infection. Additionally, avoid overcrowding plants and provide proper air circulation to reduce the likelihood of infection."}
